subSubSection.paragraph:
Chthonius guglielmii
differs from
C. ilvensis
in the following characters: setae of the carapace long and fine, the anterior ones 0.12–0.15 mm long (setae of the carapace thick, the anterior ones 0.09–0.11 mm long in
C. ilvensis
); anterior margin of carapace with 4 macrosetae, without preocular microsetae (with 1 or 2 preocular microsetae on each side in
C. ilvensis
); chelicerae mainly with 1 lateral microseta (mainly with 2 lateral microsetae in
C. ilvensis
); chela length 0.71–0.98 mm ( 0.56–0.77 mm in
C. ilvensis
); movable finger length 0.48–0.65 mm ( 0.38–0.50 mm in
C. ilvensis
); fixed finger at level of est-it with 8–11 teeth occupying 0.1 mm (with 11–14 teeth occupying 0.1 mm in
C. ilvensis
); ratio of pedipalpal femur/carapace 1.15–1.3 ( 0.95–1.15 in
C. ilvensis
); male genital opening flanked by aligned setae (by partly scattered setae in
C. ilvensis
).
